data.title: Northwestern University
data.meta_description: Eva van Agt (20) M - 2018: Earned a spot on the Second Team All-Big Ten ... Also named to the NFHCA All-West Region Second Team ... Started all 19 games and ...
data.text:
2018: Earned a spot on the Second Team All-Big Ten ... Also named to the NFHCA All-West Region Second Team ... Started all 19 games and ended the year with six goals and six assists ... Assisted on 2 goals, including the game-winner, in a 3-2 win over Boston College (9/2) ... Scored both goals in a 2-1 win over Indiana (9/14) ... Recorded assists in back-to-back contests against Michigan and Michigan State (9/28 and 9/30) ... Scored the Wildcats' only goal against Rutgers (10/12) ... Scored a goal in the final two games to close out the season against Ball State (10/21) and Michigan (10/28) ... Academic All-Big Ten.

2017: Second-team NFHCA All-West Region ... Started all 22 games ... Netted the match's lone goal in a season-opening 1-0 win over No. 13 Stanford (8/26) ... Scored OT game-winner against Ohio State (9/15) ... Recorded an assist in defeat of Rutgers to win the first round of the Big Ten Tournament (10/29) ... Ranked fourth on the team with six goals and 15 points ... Academic All-Big Ten ... NFHCA National Academic Squad ... Big Ten Distinguished Scholar.

2016: Started all 21 matches ... Named Big Ten Offensive Player of the Week Sept. 20 after posting three goals and an assist in victories at Ohio State (9/16) and Kent State (9/18) ... Academic All-Big Ten ... NFHCA National Academic Squad.

2015: Appeared in all 21 matches with 20 starts as a true freshman ... Ranked third on the team with 11 goals and 24 points ... Scored a goal in first collegiate game vs. No. 1 Connecticut (8/28) ... Posted the first goal of the match at No. 10 Maryland (9/18) ... Tallied a goal in three straight matches, all wins: at Rutgers (9/25), at Indiana (9/27), vs. Iowa (10/2) ... Scored a goal in a Big Ten tournament win over Ohio State (11/5) ... NFHCA National Academic Squad.

High School: Competed for NMHC Nymegen club team for nine years ... National training tema level A from 2012-13 ... Played in the top senior league in The Netherlands for NMHC Nymegen in 2013 and 2014 ... East-Holland All-Star team member from 2007-12 ... Team placed second in national championship in 2009 ... Also competed in cross country ... Participated in ISF Cross Country World's Schools Championships in Israel in 2014 and in Malta in 2012 ... Placed fourth in national championship for students in 2010 and 2014 ... Placed second in regional championship for students in 2009, 2010 and 2011 and third in 2013 ... Graduated magna cum laude ... Selected for the program at the Pre-University College of Science at Radboud University Nymegen.

Personal: Born Eva Margaretha van Agt ... Daughter of Frans van Agt and Judith Wielders ... Competed with NU teammates Isabel Flens and Puck Pentenga on the East-Holland All-Star team ... Grandfather, Dries van Agt, served as the Prime Minister of The Netherlands from 1977-82... Majoring in Economics and Mathematics.
